data.name: labelStart.Text
data.value: This wizard will make a virtual population analysis (VPA) on the basis of {0} catches. The basic feature of VPA is to estimate how many fish there must be in the water to account to observed numbers caught in each age group, under the assumption that natural mortality is known.

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Catches of selected gear type in different years are given in table below. Estimates of catches in values of number are given in the right column.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Numbers caught of each age group (in thous. of ind.) in previous years are given in table. Select cohort to be model for further VPA. Usually it should be an oldest cohort from most recent survey.

data.name: pageCatches.Text
data.value: Catches of age groups, thsd ind.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Age-based catches of previous years are rearranged according to certain cohorts (named by year of "birth"). These values display a history of withdraw of particular cohorts.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: Virtual population analysis is based on assumption of constant natural mortality. Provide us with known value, or (if it's unknown) click "Get M" button to estimate it.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Select particular cohort to see its history according to performed virtual population analysis. Use list to select cohort.

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: Both, catches and total size in number, of selected cohort during its lifetime are plotted on the chart below. Use list to select cohort.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: Estimated numbers of each age group (in thousands of individuals) in previous years are given in table.
